        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: hnRNP A3 is identified in PSD preparations.\nFig.3: EFGP-hnRNP A3 fusion protein localized at the tips of dendritic spines in primary neurons (mixed cort/hipp, DIV 21-28). Experimental description: 2/10/2017 Pim\n- Paper mentions accession CAA76339 for the overexpressed hnRNP A3 clone. This points to a rat sequence in NCBInr database." ;
